{
  "name": "leios_voter_two_valid_rounds",
  "description": "Voter 7 votes legitimately in two distinct pipeline rounds: the current round ($current_slot) for EB1 (hash=abab..) and a past round ($current_slot_minus_100) for EB2 (hash=cdcd..). These are different (slot, eb_hash) tuples so both votes are independently valid — the Leios spec only prohibits a voter from voting twice for the SAME (slot, eb_hash). The vote deduplication key is (voter_id, slot, eb_hash); an implementation that uses only (voter_id, eb_hash) as the key, omitting the slot dimension, would incorrectly reject voter 7's second vote because EB1 and EB2 have different hashes. More importantly, an implementation deduplicating by (voter_id, slot) and ignoring the eb_hash would reject the second vote because the slots differ. A conforming node must accept both votes and credit voter 7's weight once toward each respective EB tally. This scenario is the valid complement of leios_voter_votes_two_ebs, which tests the case where the same voter votes for two EBs in the same pipeline slot.",
  "network_magic": 42,
  "trace_output_path": "trace_leios_voter_two_valid_rounds.jsonl",
  "expected_outcome": "success",
  "sut_genesis_time_unix": 1783591775,
  "sut_slot_duration_ms": 1000,
